<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-43-0917 </DOCNO><TEXT>Volume 13 of the 'energy' manual deals with the utilization of renewableenergy sources. Reflecting the present knowledge as well as the innovationsplanned to be realized, the manual starts with an introduction and surveyof the subjects covered. Separate chapters discuss the conversion ofsolar thermal energy for low-temperature uses, medium- and high-temperaturesolar energy uses, photovoltaic solar energy uses, hydroelectric power,wind power, biomass conversion, wave power, and geothermal energy. Acomparison of alternative technical concepts and solutions helps understandand decide on the problems remaining to be solved. The manual facilitatesaccess to both essential theoretical fundamentals and practical experiences.(HWJ).</TEXT></DOC>